Let $R$ be the set of all real numbers. Define a function $f: R \to R$ that represents the sentiment of the Iranian university student towards political engagement, such that $f(x)$ is defined by the following condition:

\[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{ll}
      e^x & \text{if } x \geq 0 \\
      \ln(-x) & \text{if } x < 0 \\
\end{array} 
\right.\]

1. Prove that the function $f(x)$ is continuous for all $x \in R$.

2. Find the derivative of $f(x)$ for all $x \in R$.

3. Determine whether the function $f(x)$ is increasing or decreasing for all $x \in R$.
